The paper deals with differential privacy, which is a topic in cryptography and security (cs.CR). It also involves distributed summation and shuffling, which are topics in distributed systems (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of shuffling to simulate the Laplace mechanism involves randomness and probability, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper proposes a protocol for communication-efficient real summation, which is a topic in computer networks (cs.CC).
